  "local_port": 59076,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best interview questions asked by you ?",
  "response": "Here are some of the best interview questions I've come across, designed to gain deep insights into a candidate's skills, experience, and fit for a role:\n\n### Technical Skills\n\n1. **Coding Challenge**\n   - **Question:** Can you write a function to reverse a linked list?\n   - **Purpose:** Assesses coding skills and problem-solving ability in real-time.\n\n2. **System Design**\n   - **Question:** Design a URL shortening service like Bitly. Walk me through your thought process.\n   - **Purpose:** Evaluates the candidate's ability to design scalable systems and their understanding of key concepts like load balancing, database sharding, etc.\n\n3. **Debugging**\n   - **Question:** Here's a piece of code with a bug. Can you find and fix it?\n   - **Purpose:** Tests the candidate's ability to analyze code and troubleshoot issues.\n\n### Behavioral Skills\n\n4. **Conflict Resolution**\n   - **Question:** Can you describe a time when you faced a conflict with a team member? How did you resolve it?\n   - **Purpose:** Assesses interpersonal skills and conflict resolution abilities.\n\n5. **Adaptability**\n   - **Question:** Tell me about a time when you had to adapt to a significant change at work. How did you handle it?\n   - **Purpose:** Evaluates the candidate's flexibility and resilience.\n\n6. **Leadership**\n   - **Question:** Give an example of a project you led. What challenges did you face, and how did you overcome them?\n   - **Purpose:** Assesses leadership skills and the ability to drive projects to completion.\n\n### Problem-Solving\n\n7. **Algorithmic Thinking**\n   - **Question:** Explain how you would approach finding the nth Fibonacci number efficiently.\n   - **Purpose:** Tests algorithmic knowledge and the ability to think critically about optimization.\n\n8. **Real-World Problem**\n   - **Question:** Imagine you're tasked with improving the performance of a slow web application. What steps would you take to diagnose and solve the issue?\n   - **Purpose:** Assesses practical problem-solving skills and knowledge of performance optimization techniques.\n\n### Cultural Fit\n\n9. **Company Values**\n   - **Question:** How do you align with our company\u2019s core values of innovation, collaboration, and integrity?\n   - **Purpose:** Ensures the candidate\u2019s values align with the company\u2019s culture.\n\n10. **Work Environment**\n    - **Question:** What type of work environment brings out your best performance?\n    - **Purpose:** Helps understand if the candidate will thrive in the company\u2019s work setting.\n\nThese questions cover a range of skills and attributes that are crucial for most roles, helping to provide a comprehensive view of the candidate's suitability.",
